    "handle": "GlobalMoney",
    "text": "去美元化的开始：中国脱离美元。自2010年以来，中国的大部分跨境支付与许多国家一样，都是以美元(USD)结算的。截至2023年第一季度，情况已不再如此。在全球范围内，国际清算银行的分析显示，2022年，美元仍然是外汇结算中最常用的货币。欧元和日元分别位居第二和第三。如果人民币在全球继续升值，美元对国际贸易的束缚可能会随着时间的推移而减弱。\n\nThe Start of De-Dollarization: China’s Move Away from the USD. Since 2010, the majority of China’s cross-border payments, like those of many countries, have been settled in U.S. dollars (USD). As of the first quarter of 2023, that’s no longer the case. Globally, in 2022, the USD remained the most-used currency for FX settlements. The euro and the Japanese yen came in second and third, respectively. If the RMB’s global rise continues, the stranglehold of the USD on international trade could diminish over time.",
